///////////////////api testing with playwright/////////////////

Step 1 - Create a new folder for API Testing Project
Step 2 - Open the folder in VS Code
Step 3 - Open terminal on the location of the folder and run command  npm init playwright@latest

Step 4 - Check if demo tests are running fine using commands   npx playwright test
npx playwright test --ui
npx playwright show-report

/////////////////////playwright bdd //////////////
Step 1 - Create a new folder 
Step 2 - Open the folder in VS Code
Step 3 - Open terminal on the location of the folder and run command  npm init playwright@latest
step 4 - npm i @cucumber/cucumber
see in package.json cucumber dependencies will come
step 5 - install extension : Cucumber (Gherkin) Full Support ,to get color support
step 6 - create cucumber.json in root folder
step 7 - under test folder create two folders features and steps
step 8 - to execute npx cucumber-js test
step 9 - Once execution is complete, the report will be generated in the root directory with the name cucumber-report.html





https://www.browserstack.com/guide/playwright-cucumber
